<div id=3D"outline-container-8" class=3D"outline-2">
<h2 id=3D"8">ATD 4.1.0 - now with YAML support</h2>
<div class=3D"outline-text-2" id=3D"text-8">
<p>
Archive: <a href=3D"https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-atd-4-1-0-now-with-yaml=
-support/17982/1">https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-atd-4-1-0-now-with-yaml-s=
upport/17982/1</a>
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org5dfd34e" class=3D"outline-3">
<h3 id=3D"org5dfd34e">Martin Jambon announced</h3>
<div class=3D"outline-text-3" id=3D"text-org5dfd34e">
<p>
<a href=3D"https://github.com/ahrefs/atd">ATD</a> now has OCaml support for=
 conveniently reading data from YAML files as well as from other formats wi=
th minimal effort. It means:
</p>

<ol class=3D"org-ol">
<li>You define a <a href=3D"https://github.com/ahrefs/atd/blob/master/atd-y=
amlx/examples/app_config.atd">type for your config data</a>.</li>
<li><code>atdml --mode jsonlike app_config.atd</code> generates the OCaml c=
ode that converts a JSON-like AST containing source locations into your con=
fig data structure.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/ahrefs/atd/blob/master/atd-yamlx/examples=
/main.ml">Your program</a> loads a YAML file, converts it to a JSON-like tr=
ee, and then calls the generated function to translate it into an OCaml dat=
a structure.</li>
<li>Your application prints useful error messages if the config is malforme=
d or incomplete.</li>
</ol>

<p>
An <a href=3D"https://github.com/ahrefs/atd/blob/master/atd-yamlx/examples"=
>example</a> is included in the distribution. It uses the <a href=3D"https:=
//discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-yamlx-pure-ocaml-yaml-1-2-1-1-library/17970">rece=
ntly released YAMLx library</a>.
</p>

<p>
<span class=3D"underline">Note that YAMLx needs generous sponsors to fund t=
he work that was done and <a href=3D"https://github.com/mjambon/yamlx/blob/=
main/FUNDING.md">unlock a permissive ISC license</a> for everyone. Or you c=
an accept the terms of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GNU_Aff=
ero_General_Public_License">AGPL license</a> if you're happy to share your =
application's source code with the users.</span>
</p>

<p>
Other input file formats or other YAML libraries can be used similarly with=
 minimum effort as long as source locations are available. For this, you'll=
 need <a href=3D"https://github.com/ahrefs/atd/blob/master/atd-yamlx/src/At=
d_yamlx.ml">a bridge</a> that converts your AST into the <a href=3D"https:/=
/github.com/ahrefs/atd/blob/master/atd-jsonlike/src/AST.mli">JSON-like AST<=
/a>.
</p>
</div>
